-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Apr 22, 2025</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104ihw1665702733118.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/ihw1665702733118.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/ihw1665702733118.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"ihw1665702733118\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      unicode smp\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Include the entire Unicode range (SMP)\n </p>\n<section class=\"section refsyn\" id=\"ihw1665702733118__topic_d56090e1_d56091e1_d56092e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ihw1665702733118__p_d56093e1_d56094e1_d56095e1\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">USYS$ORA_PARAMS = unicode_smp</code>\n</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"ihw1665702733118__section_f3v_zr4_jcc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d563992e60\">Description</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ihw1665702733118__p_d56099e1_d56100e1_d56101e1\">By default, the Oracle connector allows storage only\n            of UCS-2 (or BMP) Unicode characters for the W packing code. Specify the Oracle option\n               <code class=\"ph codeph\">unicode_smp</code> to enable storage of the entire Unicode range (or SMP)\n            in W packing code fields.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ihw1665702733118__p_d56102e1_d56103e1_d56104e1\">If you use this option, UTF-16 surrogate pairs are\n            used for encoding, so 2 or 4 bytes are used to store each character.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ihw1665702733118__p_d56105e1_d56106e1_d56107e1\">For this reason, use <code class=\"ph codeph\">unicode_smp</code> only\n            if needed, for example, when working with Chinese characters, or using attributes such\n            as bold, italic, and underline.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ihw1665702733118__p_d56108e1_d56109e1_d56110e1\">More information about UTF-16 surrogate pairs is\n            available in the Internet and in the Oracle® <cite class=\"cite\">Database Globalization Support\n               Guide</cite>.</p>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2528555\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2528555\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "unicode smp Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Apr 22, 2025 Summarize Uniface 10.4 unicode smp Include the entire Unicode range (SMP) USYS$ORA_PARAMS = unicode_smp Description By default, the Oracle connector allows storage only of UCS-2 (or BMP) Unicode characters for the W packing code. Specify the Oracle option unicode_smp to enable storage of the entire Unicode range (or SMP) in W packing code fields. If you use this option, UTF-16 surrogate pairs are used for encoding, so 2 or 4 bytes are used to store each character. For this reason, use unicode_smp only if needed, for example, when working with Chinese characters, or using attributes such as bold, italic, and underline. More information about UTF-16 surrogate pairs is available in the Internet and in the Oracle® Database Globalization Support Guide . Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}